divs: Sighting DetailsOn April 10, 2002 at 5:30 A.M. CDT the witness arose and went downstairs to thekitchen and opened the blinds to look for deer on the lake on her and herhusbands property. The weather was clear. She saw a bronze metallicoctagon-shaped object about 20 feet across which seemed to float on the lake.The object had darker bronze circles around a central raised portion and anextension that appeared to have windows on it. She moved to the glass door fora better view and to make sure that what she saw wasnt a reflection orillusion. She heard no sound but watched the object for about a minute, thenran upstairs to call her husband to look. By the time the two returned theobject had disappeared. The water on the lake did not seem disturbed.
